Mahnoor sent an attachment.
Me after interacting with humans for a few hours, and now my social battery is extremely low so I need to alone quiet time to hibernate and recharge! Vulnerable mental health caption below: Since we’ve been in Dallas, I have been working with contractors and handymen and dealing with plumbers and electricians and whew it is mentally exhausting. I finally left home (the RV) and went to the store to get some supplies and was there for about 2hrs. When I got back that was it for me! I was done for the day. I think I went to bed like 7pm due to exhaustion. Just an hour of human interaction and I feel mentally exhausted which in turns feels physical and I need hours to recoup from it. Every single day I have to go in the RV and close the blinds and just lay down to recharge. Interacting with humans is exhausting! Funny enough it wasn’t always this way for me. I’m an introvert but also one who enjoyed human interaction here and there, so an ambivert really. But now I struggle with human interaction. When I say now, it’s more off over the last year and it especially got worse after losing my Dad and some other traumatic events that I had to deal with it. Andddd, all of that and more basically fried my brain. Another funny thing - my husband and son are extroverts! Hubs is out all day chatting up with people and A loves going to the local after school program at the park daily. They can interact with people all day and not feel like I do. So I let them go enjoy the outside while I stay inside. I am in therapy which really really helps and I have the most amazing therapist. I’m also making sure to give myself grace and find time to recoup as much as I can during the day. I am so thankful every single day that I live a very low maintenance and minimalistic life which allows me the opportunity to rest as needed. Some days are good, some days are bad and some days are okay. Slowly but surely I’m making strides and I’m very proud of myself! ➡️ How’s your mental health? And how are you managing it? And for those struggling like me, I’m sending you lots of love and light! We got this. Love you ❤️ #mentalhealthjourney #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthmatters

While trauma, anxiety, depression, and mental health, in general… are absolutely serious, and very important, topics… We don’t all process or deal with these experiences the same. And the reality is… if we have to deal with this BS either way… Then we might as well find a way to laugh about it simultaneously (no, I am not suggesting avoiding or minimizing our trauma or mental health struggles… I am suggesting that we can take it seriously AND laugh in the process). Furthermore, surrounding yourself with people who you don’t have to wear a mask for… you don’t have to hide any parts of you from… and you don’t fear being judged for just being you… Is by far the best feeling ever!!
